hotel: Hotel Paris Opera Affiliated by Melia
reviews:
I would like to thank Mrs Aurora and Mr Mounji for high quality services, they are really professionals. I will definitely use this Mel√≠ chain again. The breakfast was excellent and the bed was very confortabil. All the staff is very kind and polite. Thank you for your services.
Regards, Ramona Rorvik

hotel: Hotel Paris Opera Affiliated by Melia
reviews:
The location of the hotel was perfect with all the key landmarks of Paris at stone throw, either walking or by public transport. The price was reasonable for the quality and counting the nice location.
However, if there‚Äôs something I must highlight as key to the overall experience, this is the friendliness of the staff. Everyone in the team is kind and responsive. They elevate what would otherwise be just a good hotel in a great location, to an absolutely fantastic experience. Amazing team in general, and exceptional service by Azory in particular. We will be definitely staying here again whenever we return to Paris and we do recommend this hotel 100%.

hotel: Hotel Paris Opera Affiliated by Melia
reviews:
The hotel is in a fabulous location next to Grand Boulevard Metro which make travel across the city so easy.
The facilities are fabulous - a coffee machine available 24/7, Cava for guests, gorgeous rooms.
Above all the staff make it. Ishara was an absolute delight along with all of the reception team - we cannot recommend this hotel highly enough!

hotel: Hotel Paris Opera Affiliated by Melia
reviews: Fabulous staff, ultra helpful reception staff, amazing breakfast and location to die for, right beside metro grand boulevard, and round the corner from Chartiers amazing traditional French food place - well worth the queueüôåüôå

hotel: Hotel Paris Opera Affiliated by Melia
reviews: This hotel was in a great location- within a 20min walk of Gare du Nord and the Louvre. It is located on a busy street which is full of restaurants, hotels and bars. The twin room we had was great for a one night stay and though the shower is small, it was great. We arrived a couple of hours earlier than check in time but were able to check in without issue.

hotel: Hotel Paris Opera Affiliated by Melia
reviews: My husband and I stayed for a week and I have to say we will definitely return on our next Paris trip. The breakfast was delicious and it was the perfect way to start the day without feeling rushed to sit and enjoy breakfast and coffee while planning your day. During our stay the 2023 reform demonstrations were taking place and the staff went above and beyond every way possible.

hotel: Hotel Paris Opera Affiliated by Melia
reviews:
We we‚Äôre very pleased with our stay. Excellent location and very helpful staff.
We had a short stay with my teenage daughters in the Family room. Amazingly comfy beds, 2 singles were provided which was ideal rather than bunk beds. Just what was needed after a long day walking.
Staff are knowledgeable and friendly, a special Thankyou to Ishara at the door, always greeted us with a smile and made us feel welcome.
Breakfast was just right to set us up for the day.
We will definitely book again when in Paris.

hotel: Hotel Paris Opera Affiliated by Melia
reviews: A wonderful hotel in a great location just by the metro. Nice and clean. Friendly staff who were always happy to help. Nice big room with an exceptionally comfortable bed. Will definitely stay again if we return to Paris!

hotel: Hotel Paris Opera Affiliated by Melia
reviews:
Well what a find! I booked through booking.com largely on location as well as previous reviews. It lived up to our expectations and more. Firstly easily walkable to Gare du Nord, Louvre, Seine, main shopping area (15mins) Literally metro 'Grand Boulevard' outside the entrance. Located in an area with nice shops, theatre and brasseries, bistros and spoilt for choice to fit all budgets and quality of food. The hotel itself provided a lovely room, spotlessly clean although small (often seen in cities) but very well appointed. The breakfast buffet was brilliant both cooked, continental choices for all palates. Lastly the staff, so friendly switched to English easily, very helpful throughout the hotel. When asked for time of arrival I mentioned we were looking forward to celebrating my birthday and on arrival had an on ice bottle of wine and chocs!
The most telling part of teamwork is when there was an issue - when the in room safe would not open, everyone helped, it proved difficult to open the technician, reception staff did everything to get it open (contained my birthday pressie) they waited till we returned to protect our valuables and did eventually on the day open it, so relieved! Later that night arrived in our room a bouquet of flowers for the inconvenience! Just wow!
Well done to all the staff on making our stay so lovely.

hotel: Hotel Paris Opera Affiliated by Melia
reviews: This hotel will definitely not disappoint. It is in the perfect location with the metro station straight outside the front door, making it easy to get around the city with lots of nice bars and restaurants all in walking distance. The staff were all very helpful and friendly and the rooms were very clean and tidy, although a little small but this didn‚Äôt bother us as we didn‚Äôt spend much time in the room. If I return to Paris again I will definitely use this hotel. Very impressed and definitely worth the money!

hotel: Hotel Paris Opera Affiliated by Melia
reviews:
We really enjoyed our stay here whilst in Paris for 3 nights.

It was in an ideal location to walk or use the metro to get around the different landmarks in the city.

The staff and lovely and helpful despite our limited knowledge of French! Rooms were clean and tidy. We appreciated the chocolates on Valentine‚Äôs Day too. A small touch but goes a long way.

The only thing needing to change, if possible, is the shower pressure. It was hard to get a comfortable wash so we ended up having to get a bath in the end which was fine but something we aren‚Äôt used to, especially on a morning.

Thank you so much. We will recommend and use again.

hotel: Hotel Paris Opera Affiliated by Melia
reviews: This place is just fabulous. The people and the hotel are just amazing. I spent a week for my 50th birthday and I did not want to leave. I will be back in a few months. The room was so comfortable and let‚Äôs not talk about clean. I was amazed at how well kept the room was. The cleanliness of the ENTIRE hotel was so amazing. Love Love Love Love Love....

hotel: Hotel Paris Opera Affiliated by Melia
reviews:
Absolutely fantastic experience and service! Azory on night duty was exceptionally helpful!!! Will definitely be returning!!!
Breakfast was greet and location was superb!

Couldn‚Äôt have asked for anything more, and staff willing to help with any questions.

hotel: Hotel Paris Opera Affiliated by Melia
reviews: This hotel offers excellent value for its location and amenities. Most of all, the management and their team make guests' stays extra special. These commendable hosts go the extra mile to welcome and accommodate guests, all while speaking multiple languages and being very respectful of guests' needs.

hotel: Hotel Paris Opera Affiliated by Melia
reviews: This hotel exceeded all our expectations. Service was professional and polite. English was never an issue. Room (Executive windows facing to the inner ‚Äùcourt‚Äù) was surprisingly large to accomodate 3 people and the daily cleaning was excellent (in general the cleanliness in the hotel was on a very good level). Wifi worked without any problems. Breakfast buffet was a true buffet with wide variety of items. Hotel is located next to railway/metro junction with good access to pretty much everywhere.Also the large dept.stores like Printemps and Galerie Lafayette were within walking distance (~500m).The location was always crowded and there were no safety concerns whatsoever.If I need to say something negative then perhaps the temperature in the room (very warm) which - in practice - could not be adjusted but luckily we were able to open the windows.Also the room price was very high although that could have been partly explained by the Paris Motor Show event which was held exactly during the same days as our visit.I would defintely recommend this hotel if you are ready to pay for your stay.

hotel: Hotel Paris Opera Affiliated by Melia
reviews:
Lovely clean hotel, reception staff very friendly and check in was easy. Room was a good size for 2 adults and 2 children (8 & 11). No view out of the window but that didn't bother us as it meant we didn't hear much noise from the main street. Main bedroom bed was massive and very comfortable. Lovely bathroom with bath and shower. Mini bar in room and tea/coffee. Breakfast was delicious, croissants, fruits, yogurt, meats, cheese, bread or cooked breakfast. Choice of hot and cold drinks.

Location was perfect. Metro right outside the hotel but only 15-20 min walk to the main station of Chatelet les halles with direct train for the airport. Brioche Doree bakery opposite and lovely crepe place across the road too. Loads of choice for caf√©s, restaurants and small supermarkets for drinks and snacks.

Was our first trip to Paris and would definitely come back. We did the 1hr Vedettes du pont neuf Seine river cruise, climbed the steps of the Eiffel tower, hop on hop off bus to see many of the tourist sites. Went into the Louvre museum, rode on the Ferris wheel, walked to the Catacombs and Parc de Luxembourg from the hotel. Browsed the shops and had such a wonderful time.

hotel: Hotel Paris Opera Affiliated by Melia
reviews:
I recently spent four nights in this hotel with my husband and two adult children.

The hotel is well located for the RER and Metro, and within 25/30 minutes walk of Montmartre ( which incidentally I would recommend visiting only as far as the steps of Sacre Coeur ‚Ä¶ our visit was marred by very aggressive men trying to sell tourist rubbish‚Ä¶)

Nice restaurants and cafes nearby and the hotel offered some recommendations ahead of our stay.

The hotel is pleasant, with tasteful decor. The staff were friendly and helpful and the secure luggage storage was really useful before checkin and after checkout.

We had an executive king room and two superior doubles.
I think the superior double was ideal for one person, would have been a little too compact for two.
The executive king was a nice size with a nice outlook.
Rooms were clean and comfortable.

For three rooms this was not a cheap stay, but comparatively reasonable.

Only slight issues were our king room was not cleaned the first day and there was confusion from the night reception as to the reason‚Ä¶covid rules‚Ä¶although the other rooms were cleaned.
This was resolved.
Secondly the website said there would be complimentary bottled water in each room and there was not.

Overall I would recommend this lovely hotel and would stay here again.

hotel: Hotel Paris Opera Affiliated by Melia
reviews: Hotel Paris Opera was just ok for us. The location was pretty nice, which we definitely appreciated. There are some staff members that are very helpful as well. However, when we first got there our room felt like a sauna. It was completely uncomfortable. The front desk did give us a fan to carry ourselves up the stairs. The fan did help. The mattress was extremely uncomfortable as were the pillows. My husband referred to them as ‚Äúnapkin pillows‚Äù. When we asked for an extra pillow we were told there were no extras. Our stay in Paris was lovely and the hotel served its purpose- to give us a place to sleep at night. It was fine, but I wouldn‚Äôt recommend this hotel or stay here again.

hotel: Hotel Paris Opera Affiliated by Melia
reviews: Very good hotel. Lovely suite and a decent choice of breakfast at the buffet. Handily placed although further away from the Opera district than I had anticipated. It is actually placed next to Grand Boulevard metro station. Very good restaurants nearby and felt it was in a safe area of Paris.

hotel: Hotel Paris Opera Affiliated by Melia
reviews:
I booked this hotel as it was a Meli√° hotel chain. I was very dissatisfied with the accommodations. At checked in we were offered room 513 which is road facing which I requested. I did not care about noise I wanted to experience everything about Paris. And noise at night is Paris. Then they told us when they gave us our keys we were in room 407. The gentleman was kind but the lady was snooty and rude. The room was the size of a child‚Äôs bedroom and faced a dirty industrial courtyard that others could see in our room. We had to keep our drapes closed all the time. The room looked nothing like the photos.

They do not have an ice machine you need to request ice and you receive a little bit of ice hardly enough for two drinks

The next morning at 9:30 am we put a ‚Äúmake up our room‚Äù on the outside door. We returned at 6pm to our room not being cleaned and no clean dishes or linen. I went down to reception they said they would send towels. But still no clean coffee mugs or glasses.

Overall it‚Äôs an ok place to stay, location is great but you can book into the holiday inn across the street and get better rooms and experience and better price.

For a Meli√° hotel I was very dissatisfied and won‚Äôt be back again.

hotel: Hotel Paris Opera Affiliated by Melia
reviews: When we arrive at the hotel there were stains on our bed and we had a room with views to the air conditioning compressors on the second floor. We ask to change the room and they showed us an even worse room on the first floor with the compressor blocking the view of the only window it had. So we stayed on the room we were assigned first. At least they change the clothing with the stains. The second day of staying there, we ran out of shower gel. The third night, after two days of asking to change the room, they did, one on the top floor with a big terrace. If it had been change the first night our feelings about the hotel would have been different. This was supposed to be a 4 stars hotel but looked and felt like 2 stars being very generous. Terrible.

hotel: Hotel Paris Opera Affiliated by Melia
reviews:
Myself and my boyfriend stayed here in April 2022 for 3 nights. We were not expecting much due to the fair price we paid but we were very pleasantly surprised! The hotel is lovely and in a great location in Montmartre with lots going on around.

Check in was very easy and I cannot state enough how friendly, welcoming and helpful the reception staff were. They really were so welcoming and kind and could not do enough for you.

The hotel room was a decent size and very clean. Room service came everyday and the room was always spotless after. The bathroom was a decent size too and super clean.

The view from our room was amazing. It was on to the main road that the hotel was on. However, because of this view it was a bit noisy on the night if we wanted to keep the window open. We were not too bothered about this as we brought earplugs expecting there to be noise due to being in central Paris.

We thoroughly enjoyed our stay at the hotel and would definitely recommend this hotel to others. We hope to be back soon. Thank you for a lovely stay :)

hotel: Hotel Paris Opera Affiliated by Melia
reviews:
Location is lovely, close to the most attractive attractions. We could walk where we wanted. The are has loads of restaurants and bars, a very good atmosphere.

Check in was good and efficient. The lift was tiny. Our room was very cold and the windows had a constant draft: we had to keep our curtains shut. The room was small and crammed, not at all comfortable for 2 people with luggage. Cleaning was mediocre. Too few towels in a very small bathroom.

The room was noisy: we could hear the traffic and people in the streets, as well as people in the hallway. Breakfast was OK.

All in all, not worth the money we paid. Location was the biggest positive factor here!

hotel: Hotel Paris Opera Affiliated by Melia
reviews: Melia affiliated hotel. Great location in front of musee grevin and hardrock cafe. Walking distance from les grands magasins. Rooms a bit small but convenient and helping staff. Not too elaborated breakfast but good enough. Deco is cozy with parisian style details

hotel: Hotel Paris Opera Affiliated by Melia
reviews:
The hotel is very well located as you have the metro Grands Boulevards right in front of the hotel. You have a starbucks close by , the theatre trevise or theatre des vari√©t√©s really close by. But the rooms are small, the bed is awful
(Size, quality), the smell in the entire hotel is awful. The room
Are too hot and no
Posibility to have fresh air, if you open the window you have the ventilation noise. You can barely see yourself in the mirror in the main room if you want to put make up on. The bathroom
Is tiny. Bad bad

hotel: Hotel Paris Opera Affiliated by Melia
reviews: Unfortunately the room I was given resembled a cupboard, and was absolutely nothing like the photos for the room that I booked. I was really upset by this. The bathroom was extremely outdated too and the bathroom door did not actually close.

hotel: Hotel Paris Opera Affiliated by Melia
reviews:
Great for tourism and quick business trips although it can get a bit noisy due the busy area where this hotel is located.

The food is always the best of Meli√° hotels and the services were good enough. The rooms might need a refresh of design soon as they are getting a bit old by now.

hotel: Hotel Paris Opera Affiliated by Melia
reviews:
We stayed here for 3 nights. Location is great, metro station literally outside. The ladies at reception were extremely helpful. Breakfast is very average/very European. There isn‚Äôt cereals etc it‚Äôs more cheeses, ham, pastries etc. Coffee is from a machine and is very watered down.

Personally, next time I will not include breakfast as there are so many cafes on the same street. The whole hotel is VERY warm. We turned all our radiators off the minute we got there, however over night it became increasingly warm. I spoke to reception and although they weren‚Äôt able to put the air conditioning on, the did supply a large fan which did the trick.

Overall good value for money, double room was enough for us two. We had a front facing room so when you opened the doors it was very noisy however you had a lovely view so we didn‚Äôt mind.

Would definitely recommend.

hotel: Hotel Paris Opera Affiliated by Melia
reviews: All in all it was a nice stay. Maybe double check the rooms to ensure everything is working. The staff were great and we got the help we asked for. I also liked that there was 24/7 staff in the reception

hotel: Hotel Paris Opera Affiliated by Melia
reviews:
We had a very nice stay here! The room was larger than I expected. The location is great too with the metro stop just outside the doors. Plenty of restaurants around and fun shops. We didn‚Äôt have an issue with noise, but our windows didn‚Äôt open to the street.

We did have some sort of leak in our hallway. Not sure what it was, but I don‚Äôt think the lady at the front desk believed me because I said it might be coming from the AC but the AC wasn‚Äôt running. So, we just put down two towels every day to keep our young twins from slipping. That‚Äôs the only reason I took off a star.

I still wouldn‚Äôt hesitate to stay with them again. It was a nice place overall. The gentleman that checked us is was extremely nice and pleasant to deal with.

hotel: Hotel Paris Opera Affiliated by Melia
reviews: Clean and rooms, surprisingly very quiet inside the rooms especially being just off the high street/next to a pub. Really lovely place to get some rest after a full day of walking/touring Paris. Located right near a metro station to get to anything not within walking distance.

hotel: Hotel Paris Opera Affiliated by Melia
reviews: Had a lovely trip, staff were so helpful and welcoming. Lovely breakfast there was a lot of choice, great selection of pastries. Also breakfast finished not too early too (10:30). The room was very clean and modern.

hotel: Hotel Paris Opera Affiliated by Melia
reviews:
The hotel is small as you may expect from the location. Rooms clean, good service, staff well trained and kind. They remained helpful and cooperative during our stay. Breakfast not worth including in the stay, the location is full of options.

Good place if you want to stay in tje Opera zone of Paris.

hotel: Hotel Paris Opera Affiliated by Melia
reviews: If you're visiting Paris to explore the city, this is the ideal hotel for you to stay. With the Metro located right in front of the hotel's doorstep, you can visit any place you want to with great convenience. The room was modern and immaculate. I had the room with a balcony facing the street and I loved it! The staff are very friendly and helpful. Overall I had a wonderful experience with Hotel Paris Opera.

hotel: Hotel Paris Opera Affiliated by Melia
reviews: The whole experience was missing: no cold water in the bathroom, only super hot! very hot room, tiny and expensive for the basic service provided. It could be an average 3 star. English language barely spoken, it is a Spanish Hotel with groups and messy "lobby". We won't be back for sure

hotel: Hotel Paris Opera Affiliated by Melia
reviews: The rooms are very hot, and the courtyard outside is very noisy so opening the window is not really an option. Also, the room was very tatty - lots of broken furniture items, broken shower screen, etc

hotel: Hotel Paris Opera Affiliated by Melia
reviews: The room was spacious and cleaned very well each day (we stayed 6 nights during Christmas, December 2019). The breakfasts were good. The location was very convenient for nice long walks to the Louvre, Opera National De Paris, the Eiffel Tower and many fine eating establishments (especially Creme de Paris). What really made this hotel standout was the staff. Many, many thanks to the ever-patient and helpful Cesar, and the lovely Isabel. We hope to return!

hotel: Hotel Paris Opera Affiliated by Melia
reviews:
Hotel is well located and has Metro entry in front of the door.
Rooms and bathroom are clean but are rather small for 4* hotel.
Rooms facing street are quite noisy.
Breakfast is quite ok but is not upto the level one would expect from a 4*.
So in short, Hotel Paris Opera would be an excellent choice for a 3* hotel but not if you expect 4*...

hotel: Hotel Paris Opera Affiliated by Melia
reviews: The hotel is located in a nice and central suburb. The room, although extremely small, was overall modern and clean. The staff was pretty helpful and kind. The breakfast was good and various. All in all, I would recommend it.

hotel: Hotel Paris Opera Affiliated by Melia
reviews: Great hotel, friendly staff, absolutely no complaints. Great location and breakfast was good. I highly recommend this hotel. In particular the room was comfy and the staff were very friendly and helpful

hotel: Hotel Paris Opera Affiliated by Melia
reviews: High Price and Average Quality. Almost No amenities in the room and the bathroom! A single room incl. breakfast cost almost 200 Euro per night. The location is great just by the metro station and the breakfast was not excellent but it was okay. For the money paid and 4-star hotel it was significantly below expectations.

hotel: Hotel Paris Opera Affiliated by Melia
reviews: The hotel is very well located. The staff were really great hosts. Clean room, delicious food, customer service over all was above expectations. Always communicating weather info and guiding US. Highly recommended!!

hotel: Hotel Paris Opera Affiliated by Melia
reviews:
I loved my stay here, it is in a great location just opposite a Metro and a short walking distance from the Louvre. We stayed in a standard room with a beautiful, apartment vibe and luxury interior.

The staff are polite and the overall quality of the hotel is definitely 4 - 5 stars.

hotel: Hotel Paris Opera Affiliated by Melia
reviews: This hotel is right in front of Grands Boulevards Metro station so moving around Paris is a breeze. Surrounded by restaurants and Galleries La Fayette is just a short walk away. Rooms are clean and staffs are helpful and polite. The only downside is the noise from the street especially on weekend nights.

hotel: Hotel Paris Opera Affiliated by Melia
reviews: Service was excellent, breakfast superb, bed comfortable, location fabulous. Our only caveat is the noise level from the Boulevard Montmartre. Even on a Sunday, people were partying across the street until about 3:30 a.m., so be forewarned, and if possible, get a room that doesn't look out onto the street. That being said, because the bed was so comfortable, we managed to get a good sleep despite the noise, so maybe you can chance it.

hotel: Hotel Paris Opera Affiliated by Melia
reviews: The hotel is amazing the loft was very gorgeous and the rooms were very clean to use and the wine of the rooms were good and the bed was very soft and gentle I liked how the hotel work and I recommend every single person to go there once

hotel: Hotel Paris Opera Affiliated by Melia
reviews:
We came for a few days to Paris and decided to stay at this great hotel. The Premium Fitness Room is awesome and very comfortable. Thank you Daniel SY for everything!

The room has a Nesspresso machine, flat TV, a spacious bathroom and a huge King Size bed. 100% recommended!

hotel: Hotel Paris Opera Affiliated by Melia
reviews: This was an excellent hotel. It was close to all the sights we wanted to see. The area was very nice, it was enjoyable just to walk around the neighbourhood. The hotel staff were very friendly and welcoming. The room, although small by North American standards was clean and comfortable. I would definitely come back.

hotel: Hotel Paris Opera Affiliated by Melia
reviews: I were going a weekend to Paris and had points that I need to spend. I therefor booked on night at this hotel. It was supposed to be a standard double room, there was bearly enough space on the floor between the wall and the bed to be able to open the suite case, but then it was not possible to move around in the room. I have been staying at Melia hotels in many countries, and if this is the standard that Melia allows their hotels to have on the rooms, then the stadard has fallen drastically. On the positive side, the bed was good to sleep in and the breakfast was ok.

hotel: Hotel Paris Opera Affiliated by Melia
reviews: I've been in several Melia hotel in Spain and Europe, and this hotel doesn't reach the Melia Standards. There was a leak on the room I mention it to the cleaner and reception and when I came back the leak still there..... and the shower has black mold in the walls.

hotel: Hotel Paris Opera Affiliated by Melia
reviews: In Paris, esp. for average price, you expect little tiny rooms, with a bathroom where you can hardly stand ... This Melia is a very positive surprise ... Rooms are really big for Paris, with a fitness bike, big bathroom, very comfortable ! Located in an animated area of Paris, easy to reach. Very decent breakfast too. Well, just a good choice.

hotel: Hotel Paris Opera Affiliated by Melia
reviews: My daughter husband and I had 2 rooms booked for the weekend on the Bastille in July. Both small rooms on the 5 th floor. The clerk checking us in was very good as we're all the staff. The first night was good but during the second the room became warm. And I mentioned this but was told it would be fine. Returning to our room in the evening the air con was not working and had in fact broken down. We spent a very uncomfortable night as did many other people. No advantage being silver card holders. Felt as though a refund should have been given . Definitely would not stop in this Melia when in Paris.

hotel: Hotel Paris Opera Affiliated by Melia
reviews:
It is a very Old building converted into a hotel. I didn‚Äôt like this hotel. Hallways are narrow the rooms are very, very small. They are not rooms for humans.
I have never experienced a deceptive accomadations like that,and I am not a big hotel snob.
it is a 2 Stars hotel does not deceive anyone as a 4-Star hotel in the future.The rooms are tiny, dirty, and loud, and the bathrooms were unclean. If your only concern spending as little as possible for a spot to lay down, then this place is for you. If you want to sleep well or hang out in your room, look elsewhere. This should not really be called a "hotel"
Safety box did not work They brought one later ( See attached pictures)
Confusing layout. I had been given a smaller room, then I booked. I Contact the Manager! Demand the he Owner to Place Me in Another Room. He Didn‚Äôt Want to But After A Few Emails Was Exchanged and calls of great the customer service of booking site, he Finally Place Me in Right Room. At check out the receptionist made mistakes and He made me pay for city tax for two persons while I was one person and informed me then I sent a claim to the hotel manager and did not get the reply so far. I will never recommend anyone nor I will ever stay there. The most horrible motel experience ever!!

hotel: Hotel Paris Opera Affiliated by Melia
reviews: Hotel Opera Meliia should be your first choice when visiting Paris The hotel is quite small and very well-maintained. all staff wonderfully nice speak Spanish and English. If your room facing the boulevard -well, obviously some traffic noise- bring earplugs. Regular guest since 2010.

hotel: Hotel Paris Opera Affiliated by Melia
reviews: Located centrally, near 19c arcades full of interesting shops and restaurants, close to major department stores. A metro station right outside the hotel. Comfortable, quiet rooms and efficient air conditioning

hotel: Hotel Paris Opera Affiliated by Melia
reviews: Stayed here for 3 nights. It‚Äôs a very cute hotel upon arriving. Inside is very modern interior and good mix with some older styles. The rooms are tiny. It fits the bed, a small desk and night stand. The bathroom was even smaller, I get it though, not much space in Paris and they have to get as much in as they can. The good: the location is perfect! Literally in front of the hotel is a metro station and bus station. There are a hundred restaurants and bars within a 5 minute walking radius. There is also a small grocery store half a block away which is nice to have. The staff were awesome, they helped us with any questions had. We also bought a bottle of wine to have one night, but realized we didn‚Äôt have a corkscrew and they happily got one and gave us a couple of wine glasses. Now I know the hotel can‚Äôt control this, but the AC broke down on the hottest day of the year. The staff did the best they could and did get it up and running again around 11 pm. Okay hotel other than that. Nothing I haven‚Äôt mentioned already to make it worthwhile to go again.

hotel: Hotel Paris Opera Affiliated by Melia
reviews: This is our second time at this hotel. Arrived early after international flight from US. Because of this and the fact that hotel was entirely booked, they couldn't accommodate early check in. Other than that, the staff was extremely helpful with our luggage, directions, arranging for taxi, etc; the rooms were clean and well-kept. Wi-fi worked without a problem. Breakfast was varied and of good quality, and they were able to prepare some earlier than usual to accommodate an early departure. The hotel is right by the Metro station, conveniently located -it's about a 30min walk to Notre-Dame, 15min to the Louvre.

hotel: Hotel Paris Opera Affiliated by Melia
reviews:
Booked as part of a British Airways weekend package (a birthday gift from my partner), the hotel is very conveniently located for the Metro and also the OpenTour sightseeing bus (stop just opposite). Also, walking distance (20 mins) from Galeries Lafayette and Printemps at Opera.
We asked for a quiet twin bedded room and were told that all of the twin-bedded were at the front of the hotel. OUr room was spacious, recently renovated and spotless. However, when we returned after dinner to go to sleep, we discovered that one floor below us and immediately next door was an Irish Pub with loud music WHICH CLOSED AT 0600 hrs IN THE MORNING. We could almost hear every word of conversation (most of it shouted loudly) that took place throughout the night -- not to mention the car hooting and motor bike revving. My partner, literally, got NO sleep -- eventually phoning the Night Porter at 0300hrs and saying we needed to move room the next day. This was eventually arranged the next morning but we had to have separate rooms. There was further confusion as to how long this would need to be for -- but eventually it was for the remainder of our stay (3 further nights).

There was an apology from the staff -- who mostly were very pleasant and helpful -- but clearly the hotel knows what that room is like and it should never be rented.

The other extremely annoying thing was that almost every time one returned to the hotel and went to (whichever) room one was occupying, the electronic pass key didn't work and one had to come back down and get it revalidated. We saw the same thing happening to other customers as well. On top of everything else, NOT something which improved my view of the place.

Overall, the hotel had much to recommend it but you need to be certain that you get a room which is NOT at the front on the main street.

hotel: Hotel Paris Opera Affiliated by Melia
reviews:
We enjoyed an excellent stay at the Hotel Paris Opera. The hotel staff couldn't have been better.
The room and hotel were very clean and we felt very safe and secure throughout our stay.

The hotel's location is great, a few blocks from the Paris Opera. The Metro station and taxis were at the hotel's door and good restaurants nearby.

The only con I can add is that the breakfast although very good was a bit costly even by Paris standards, 16 Euro per person per day if you sign up for your full stay or 20 Euros if you pay daily.

Overall we had great stay and we will definitely stay there on our next trip

hotel: Hotel Paris Opera Affiliated by Melia
reviews: Good location, within walking distance to main museums, restaurants and shops. very friendly staff and servers. clean room and bathroom . quite a bit traffic but that is to be expected if you want to be where all the attractions are.

hotel: Hotel Paris Opera Affiliated by Melia
reviews:
Great location but the hotel rooms/bathroom, especially the shower, was too small.
The staff was great, very friendly and helpful.
The hotel is right outside a metro stop and walking distance from the Opera!

hotel: Hotel Paris Opera Affiliated by Melia
reviews:
We stayed in Room 101 for 3 nights & it lived up to its Orwellian reputation (√° la 1984).

This hotel is billed as a 4* but the room was tiny, no bigger - and quite possibly smaller - than a typical Ibis hotel room.

The room was uncomfortably warm. The aircon didn't work and the window could not be opened more than an inch or two due to the location of the desk/dressing table in the room. But that didn't matter as outside the window an enormous, metallic exhaust/vent protruding out of an adjacent wall of the hotel exhaled so much noise all through the night, that opening the window for ventilation was not a feasible option!

Also, the toilet blocked twice.

I hope the hotel management doesn't respond to this review by saying that I should have raises these matters with them, as surely the management should have known about these issues and either done something about them or left the rooms affected empty until they were fixed.

As you can see I am extemely disappointed. I was ready to share my feelings with the management at checkout time but the person who was dealing with me was distracted by dealing with another guests' issues and didn't even get round to asking me whether everything had been OK during our stay!

On the upside, the young man who checked us in was polite & well trained, the Grands Boulevards Metro station is, literally, right outside the hotel's entrance and the surrounding area has a huge choice of bars, bistros and restaurants to choose from.

hotel: Hotel Paris Opera Affiliated by Melia
reviews: Great location for Opera etc and good amenities but is on a very busy street with an Irish bar underneath and an Australian bar opposite.: very noisy until 4am. Air con out of order the whole period of our visit.

hotel: Hotel Paris Opera Affiliated by Melia
reviews: It was a great location in the city. Metro station right outside the front door. Staff was always kind and extremely helpful. Loved the cafes and restaurants within walking distance. The neighborhood was lively. Highly recommended hotel.

hotel: Hotel Paris Opera Affiliated by Melia
reviews:
Quite small hotel but rooms are spacious, comfortable and very clean. Only the shower head is small. It has very narrow corridors to get to the rooms. One tiny lift.
It has some family feel, you feel like at home rather than in a hotel. The breakfast is very nice, with a strong Spanish touch..

Staff are very nice and friendly. It is surrounded by lots of restaurants, pubs and some shops.

The entrance is literally a few meters away from the underground entrance. And there is a taxi rank just outside the hotel. In my previous stay they ordered a private car to take me to the airport (Charles de Gaulle) first thing in the morning and it was just ‚Ç¨60 instead of ‚Ç¨50 with a normal cab.

As it is near my office, opposite the Stock Exchange (La Bourse), I will most likely stay there again for a 3rd time

hotel: Hotel Paris Opera Affiliated by Melia
reviews:
I have been coming to Paris a few times a year for 15 years, always looking for a good hotel. This one had a sale and was very convenient to where I had to work. The place is fine, it simply needs renovation. Everything in the room looked worn. In the bathroom, there was water damage on the door frame of the bathroom; "chrome" soap holders warn down to plastic; makeup mirror wobbly. Everything was perfectly clean and comfortable but I am not sure I would have been happy if I hadn't gotten the discount.
I had a room in the back which was very very quiet. The hotel overall has a nice layout so that no one's room is near the elevator. A colleague had a room to the front though and found it very noisy on the weekend. But he wasn't too bothered.
The one thing I would really liked changed was that I rarely saw staff behind the desk look up when I entered or left the hotel. When there was a doorman, he had a warm smile and was welcoming. However, I never felt the rest of the staff was keeping an eye on the comings and goings of the hotel.

hotel: Hotel Paris Opera Affiliated by Melia
reviews:
The service and breakfast were both great, but the hotel is undergoing renovations and I believe that our floor should have been closed while that was completed. The hallways were covered in plastic. it was kind of tacky, particularly by Parisian standards.

Our room had clearly been recently renovated as well, but quite poorly. The laminate flooring had a big gap where the pieces didn‚Äôt quite line up, and the tile work in the washroom was done by someone who doesn‚Äôt know how to lay tile. It looks like they have their in-house maintenance crew do everything rather than contracting the work out to qualified tradespeople. It isn‚Äôt good, it‚Äôs ‚Äúgood enough.‚Äù

It was very loud out on the street on the Saturday night, but I can‚Äôt fault the hotel for that. If noise is an issue for you though I‚Äôd recommend requesting a room on the back side if possible.

hotel: Hotel Paris Opera Affiliated by Melia
reviews: We had a wonderful time in Paris . The hotel. Treated us like family. I would definitely stay there again. The warmth of the staff the comfort of the room were perfect. Loved the heated towels in the bathroom over all very satisfied

hotel: Hotel Paris Opera Affiliated by Melia
reviews: My mother and I had a wonderful time at this hotel. We definitely plan to stay here again in the future. Brice, Cesar, Sylvia and Aurora were phenomenal. They really made us feel welcomed and were attentive!

hotel: Hotel Paris Opera Affiliated by Melia
reviews:
It was my first time in Paris. May be was me, but rooms were really small. Bathroom was a reall cramped space.
There was no good option for vegitarian in breakfast.
Front desk service were poor, when we landed there was no one to help us with the doors.
Only one lift was working, it too was very narrow.

hotel: Hotel Paris Opera Affiliated by Melia
reviews: I have been a guest of Hotel Paris Opera for over 20 years, and every time I go I find a family welcome, it is the only hotel that I feel at home away from home and I recommend it to anyone who wants to have an unforgettable experience

hotel: Hotel Paris Opera Affiliated by Melia
reviews: Was in Melia Opera two weeks ago. It‚Äôs perfectly located near Boulevard Haussmann and metro access to Grands Boulevard directly in front of the hotel door. Rooms are clean and fit for purpose. Breakfast is very good, with a wide selection.

hotel: Hotel Paris Opera Affiliated by Melia
reviews:
Very nice hotel and perfectly suited for a business trip. Plenty of good restaurants nearby for evenings. A little loud at night being in a main road but didn‚Äôt affect my sleep.

Breakfast was more than enough but if I was on holiday I think it wouldn‚Äôt have felt like enough of a treat to choose over other local options. Nice enough though.

All in a good hotel in a convenient and nice location!

hotel: Hotel Paris Opera Affiliated by Melia
reviews: The hotel was in a handy location for the main stations but is on a noisy road and next to a noisy Irish Pub! We didn't have the most comfortable nights sleep either. The staff were welcoming and friendly.

hotel: Hotel Paris Opera Affiliated by Melia
reviews:
The room was spacious for Paris hotels. I had more than the basic room with two windows overlooking the busy street. The double glazed windows blocked the street noise well. Comfortable bed and a reasonable bathroom with separate toilet.
The breakfast was good. The staff friendly and helpful. I would recommend this hotel to family and friends.

hotel: Hotel Paris Opera Affiliated by Melia
reviews:
We stayed in room 408 (we booked a standard twin room) for 4 nights in mid-April. The location is fantastic, with a metro station directly outside and within walking distance to many shops and restaurants. The staff at the front desk were all very friendly and welcoming.

The room was extremely small, even by Paris standards, but the bed was OK. The main problem we encountered is that the air conditioning was totally ineffective. We had the misfortune to visit during a rare April heat wave, and even with the window open it was difficult to sleep. In addition, it was simply too small for two people with luggage, so that added to the lack of comfort.

If I stayed here again, I would definitely pay extra for a premium room or a suite, even if I were traveling alone.

hotel: Hotel Paris Opera Affiliated by Melia
reviews: This trip was our fifth time staying at this hotel. We have always felt at home here yet the hotel manages to keep improving, The strongest asset is the welcoming staff. (They even offered me honey when I had a sore throat). In many other ways the staff went above and beyond to help us too. In addition, the facility has been renovated to offer a sleek yet comfortable ambience. The rooms are well laid out with several amenities (coffee maker, minibar, etc.) Finally, the location is superb for visiting any place in Paris.

hotel: Hotel Paris Opera Affiliated by Melia
reviews: Nice hotel well located clean with a good breakfast simple but very healthy and for me is enough. Everybody in the hotel very polite and I really recommend this hotel. If i wiil go again to Paris probably choose this hotel again even that is not a new hotel

hotel: Hotel Paris Opera Affiliated by Melia
reviews: the hotel is very practical in the heart of Paris, close to Bourse, Opera and Les Halles. The rooms are OK but would benefit from double glazed windows in view of the noisy street below. The meeting room meets its purpose and the service good.

hotel: Hotel Paris Opera Affiliated by Melia
reviews:
They have a double room suite (2x2 beds) that is perfect for a family. 1 king bed + a bunk in 2 rooms.
The reception is a little bit shabby, but it is perfectly located for tourism.
Most of the staff is also Spanish speaking.

hotel: Hotel Paris Opera Affiliated by Melia
reviews: I think the location was good for the Palais Brongniart where my event was and it was on a road with many bars and restaurants. The room was lovely - I sprang for the fitness room - but there was one major drawback. It was incredibly loud. The external door doesn‚Äôt seem to be snug tight to the wall so there was a lot of hallway sound - once or twice I actually got up to double check someone hadn‚Äôt come in. And the windows cannot be double glazed because Street noise is horrendous. Sirens woke me up, hoardes of people shouting kept me from getting to sleep. I know the protests are happening but there was also music from the pub next door (open until 5.30am) and sounds of multiple fights. It was so loud I had trouble sleeping - if you‚Äôre there on business I would insist on a room on the other side of the building. I was in 504.

hotel: Hotel Paris Opera Affiliated by Melia
reviews: Staff very friendly and cooperative. Location good but rooms can be warm as there is no AC in the winter months but a fan (based on a timer) can be supplied. Rooms facing onto the street can be noisy at night with the pub next door

hotel: Hotel Paris Opera Affiliated by Melia
reviews: Great location, basic... that‚Äôs where it ends. If you‚Äôre going to refurbish a hotel at least close or ventilate until the paint fumes are no longer going to make your guests suffer! Won‚Äôt be selecting this one again

hotel: Hotel Paris Opera Affiliated by Melia
reviews: My wife and I celebrated our 30th wedding anniversary in Paris in October 2018 and spent 6 nights at Hotel Paris Opera by Melia. The hotel is centrally located near all the popular tourist attractions, i.e. Louvre, Notre Dame, Musee d'Orsay, Arc de Triomphe. Highly recommend using the metro pass since the metro station is just outside the hotel entrance. The hotel provided a nice breakfast buffet and the staff was friendly and attentive. If you are looking for a comfortable place to stay while visiting the sites in Paris, I would recommend this hotel. The hotel does not have many amenities like a resort however you are very close to restaurants and bars and we did not spend much time at the hotel. The staff also surprised us with a complimentary bottle of champagne to celebrate our anniversary, a very nice touch. We would stay at the Hotel Paris Opera again based on the price and location.

hotel: Hotel Paris Opera Affiliated by Melia
reviews: Excellent, friendly staff and a great location. Taxi and metro literally just outside the front door. Good breakfast with plenty of choice of hot cooked food and the usual pastries. Very child friendly. We appreciated the Halloween candy, decoration and wishes!

hotel: Hotel Paris Opera Affiliated by Melia
reviews: Room was clean and hotel truly centrally located. Staff helpful and friendly. However, this is most definitely NOT a four star hotel. Room is small, bathroom shower gives new meaning to word tiny. Had to stand in place to take a shower, barely any room to move. Room clean but looks refurbished. Stayed five days, was without air conditioning for four days. Slept with windows open. Room faced street and was very noisy all night. Bed was comfortable. Breakfast standard fare. Looking for just bare bone lodging? you found it. Looking for four star? keep looking. Will not stay there again

hotel: Hotel Paris Opera Affiliated by Melia
reviews: Hotel is in a really great location in Paris with lot's of action. 10 minute walk to Louvre. We stayed for 5 days. Rooms we had had been renovated and were very nice. Hotel staff very friendly and helpful. Good breakfast. Really enjoyed and highly recommend.

hotel: Hotel Paris Opera Affiliated by Melia
reviews: We stayed at the Hotel Paris Opera for 10 days. The room was spotless, bed was comfortable. We were on the 4th floor and the view was lovely. The windows open! Floor to ceiling windows. Staff was polite and spoke English. Breakfast was much better than I expected, eggs, bacon, sausage, croissants, yogurt, fruit and veggies! We would stay here again.

hotel: Hotel Paris Opera Affiliated by Melia
reviews: my room faced onto the street and was so noisy I could not sleep, indeed it was so bad one night I got up to check the windows were actually closed. Rooms are basic but clean. Breakfast was fine. Would be good to have a hotel bar

hotel: Hotel Paris Opera Affiliated by Melia
reviews: Small hotel with a a friendly conduction. In a nice and central area of paris. Good and rich breakfast. Nice waiter and good double espresso. They please every request and need. Nice bed and conmfortable matress.

hotel: Hotel Paris Opera Affiliated by Melia
reviews: Very noisy because of work until 9pm in the building beside. Very very small room. I never saw a small bed like that. No advantage of having Melia card. Poor and no variety in the breakfast.only location is great

hotel: Hotel Paris Opera Affiliated by Melia
reviews: Located in Montmartre, Opera is walking distance to nearly everything while perched on a subway line, taxi queue and multiple bus routes. Nearby are all the bars and quality restaurants you could want, while the breakfast buffet is plentiful and staff exceptionally friendly and helpful 24-7. Room is reasonably small but clean and well-laid out - bathroom and shower separate; the only knock is noise at night, which can last to 3 or 4 in the morning, and sounded like Paris heading back to the barricades. Still, I‚Äôd stay there again and recommended for reasonable price and great service.

hotel: Hotel Paris Opera Affiliated by Melia
reviews:
The positives of the hotel are the kind employees, the location close to the opera and almost in from of the metro, the good led tvs and the decor is ok. On the aspects that should be improved I want to stress the toillet that is really small and the breakfast for a 4 star is short this way beyond the good croissants in 5 days only one had natural pinapple one day and the range was limited. Addionally if your room window is directed to interior courtyard the AC system can be a bit noisy.
Bottom line this hotel is managed by melia but was a tryp and a tryp is from a different price tag of a melia that's why I give 4 out 5, if it was a real melia I would give 3

hotel: Hotel Paris Opera Affiliated by Melia
reviews:
My wife and I stayed here for 4 days and enjoyed our stay.

It is well located with a metro stop right out the front of the hotel.

We liked the boutique feel of the hotel and loved its location in an area full of cafes, restaurants and bars.

We stayed on the second floor in room 205, which had a balcony that enabled us to look out onto the tree lined The Boulevard which immediately made us feel that we were in Paris.

If you are a light sleeper then the noise from the Irish Pub next door and The Oz Bar across the road could be probematic, however we were so tired from our daily activities that it didn't bother us and we are in our late 60's.

We really enjoyed the buffet breakfast each morning.

We found the staff to be generally very helpful.

We would definitely stay there again.

hotel: Hotel Paris Opera Affiliated by Melia
reviews: We've stayed in this hotel in August of 2016, and August of 2018, nothing changed. Toilet doesn't work, we've called 3 times to fix it, and ended up fixing it ourselves for good. It works now! Misty smell in the rooms. This is a solid 3 star hotel, not 4. We've been to Melia managed hotels and resorts in Cancun, Mexico, as well as others, and this is just a dated 3 star hotel. Hotel staff is very professional, accommodating, and speaks good English. Metro station is just right in front of the hotel. This is the main reason that we've selected it for the second time, since it is so convenient!

hotel: Hotel Paris Opera Affiliated by Melia
reviews:
My daughters stayed here for a night to explore Paris.

The staff at the hotel were very nice and looked after them well. The hotel was very nice and the room comfortable.

It is in a great position for exploring Paris and very reasonable.

Thanks for looking after my girls so well

hotel: Hotel Paris Opera Affiliated by Melia
reviews: Overall the location was very central to lots of restaurants, metro and even hop on/off bus. The experience at this hotel was it cover our basic needs but with some undesirable problems. This included shower was very small and I was barely able to get into it. Also the shower drain was clogged, sink was cracked and leaked, Our safe did not work after advising them a number of times. Note that rooms are directly above a bar and it can get very noisy at night, bars close at 4:30am. I would say this is a 3 star hotel. If we could remove some of the maintenance issues, it may have been a better stay. Personally I would not stay here again and would consider better options.

hotel: Hotel Paris Opera Affiliated by Melia
reviews:
I've been there in my honeymoon and I have really enjoy my stay. Rooms are really tidy and the hotel is in an excellent position to reach the center of the city either by metro (the Grand Boulevards station is exactly in front offline the hall) or by feet (the Louvre is only a 20 minutes far from the hotel).
The staff is very kind, attentive and helpfull!
Very recommended!

hotel: Hotel Paris Opera Affiliated by Melia
reviews: With just myself & my husband the location of this hotel was great. It was within a 10 minute walk of Opera & Gallerie Lafayette. There are plenty of places to eat & drink in the nearby area. There is a Metro station just outside the hotel (takes a while to get used to shake of the building) There is also a Big Bus hop on & off bus stop just across the road. The hotel was clean & friendly in an old building the rooms did not have the finesse I would expect from a Melia hotel but it is in Paris & I have never found the star rating to be reliable there. Breakfast was good but busy periods should be avoided as there is no room to move. The staff are friendly and helpful, the period we were there the main visitors were Spanish. I would recommend this hotel for an adult city break.

hotel: Hotel Paris Opera Affiliated by Melia
reviews: Steps leading to the metro are right outside the hotel, making it easy to sight see and go from place to place. Lots of restaurants up and down the street. Nice accommodations and a very pleasant room.
